{"name":"stcor: Correlograms of Space-Time ARIMA","tagline":"r, arima, space-time, time series, package","body":"Description\r\n=====\r\nThe `stcor` package provides functions for correlograms of the advanced time series model, the Space-Time Autoregressive Integrated Moving Average (STARIMA). These functions are the Space-Time Autocorrelation Function (`stacf`) and Space-Time Partial Autocorrelation Function (`stpacf`). Including function for centralizing (`stcenter`) the data to its mean.\r\n\r\nInstallation\r\n-----\r\n```{coffee}\r\nif (!require(\"devtools\"))\r\n  install.packages(\"devtools\")\r\ndevtools::install_github(\"stcor\", \"alstat\")\r\n```\r\n\r\n***\r\nVignette\r\n-----\r\nTo start with, let us simulate a space-time series. Assuming there are seven (7) spatial locations with 155 observation. Then we have,\r\n```{coffee}\r\nseries <- arima.sim(list(order = c(2,0,0),\r\n                    ar = c(0.7, -0.5)), n = 155)\r\n\r\nlocation1 <- series + rnorm(length(series))\r\nlocation2 <- series + rnorm(length(series))\r\nlocation3 <- series + rnorm(length(series))\r\nlocation4 <- series + rnorm(length(series))\r\nlocation5 <- series + rnorm(length(series))\r\nlocation6 <- series + rnorm(length(series))\r\nlocation7 <- series + rnorm(length(series))\r\n```\r\nNow we will merge this into a data frame object,\r\n```{coffee}\r\nseries.df <- data.frame(location1, location2, location3,\r\n                        location4, location5, location6,\r\n                        location7)\r\n```\r\nAnd it is required to centralize the data to its mean,\r\n```{coffee}\r\nseries.df <- stcenter(series.df)\r\n```\r\nThen assuming the spatial neighbourhood of our data has the following weights matrices,\r\n\r\n* Weights matrix for first spatial order\r\n\r\n```{coffee}\r\nW1 <- rbind(c(0,0,0,0,0,1,0),\r\n            c(0,0,0,1,0,0,0),\r\n            c(0,0,0,1,0,0,0),\r\n            c(0,1/3,1/3,0,0,1/3,0),\r\n            c(0,0,0,0,0,1/2,1/2),\r\n            c(1/4,0,0,1/4,1/4,0,1/4),\r\n            c(0,0,0,0,1/2,1/2,0))\r\n```\r\n* Weights matrix for second spatial order\r\n\r\n```{coffee}\r\nW2 <- rbind(c(0,0,1/3,1/3,0,0,1/3),\r\n            c(0,0,1/2,0,0,1/2,0),\r\n            c(1/3,1/3,0,0,0,1/3,0),\r\n            c(1/3,0,0,0,1/3,0,1/3),\r\n            c(0,0,0,1,0,0,0),\r\n            c(0,1/2,1/2,0,0,0,0),\r\n            c(1/2,0,0,1/2,0,0,0))\r\n```\r\n* Weights matrix for third spatial order\r\n\r\n```{coffee}\r\nW3 <- rbind(c(0,1/2,0,0,1/2,0,0),\r\n            c(1/3,0,0,0,1/3,0,1/3),\r\n            c(0,0,0,0,1/2,0,1/2),\r\n            c(0,0,0,0,0,0,0),\r\n            c(1/3,1/3,1/3,0,0,0,0),\r\n            c(0,0,0,0,0,0,0),\r\n            c(0,1/2,1/2,0,0,0,0))\r\n```\r\n\r\nFinally we compute the STACF and STPACF\r\n```{coffee}\r\nstacf(data = series.df, wmatrices = list(NULL, W1, W2, W3))\r\n```\r\n\r\n```{coffee}\r\n      Spatial Lag 0 Spatial Lag 1 Spatial Lag 2 Spatial Lag 3\r\n [1,]    0.28695206   0.345832479   0.339044188   0.283588608\r\n [2,]   -0.15742990  -0.191470226  -0.179197661  -0.162677077\r\n [3,]   -0.31668424  -0.330822265  -0.340232224  -0.290509039\r\n [4,]   -0.14868812  -0.157455030  -0.153290425  -0.132021031\r\n [5,]    0.03591543   0.013410038   0.010782729   0.044738385\r\n [6,]    0.06047440   0.052261004   0.083377691   0.063055773\r\n [7,]    0.01456504   0.026772376   0.016847440   0.047956766\r\n [8,]   -0.01181031  -0.009140694  -0.005078934  -0.034661364\r\n [9,]   -0.10570392  -0.102730730  -0.095261483  -0.089881169\r\n[10,]   -0.06708123  -0.087271392  -0.085602456  -0.086916228\r\n[11,]    0.03421200   0.041693191   0.042132363   0.034122235\r\n[12,]    0.12144821   0.130752971   0.137245696   0.127726621\r\n[13,]    0.05167491   0.088064307   0.076911135   0.069112356\r\n[14,]   -0.02158922  -0.021445410  -0.017272300  -0.009322154\r\n[15,]   -0.10197071  -0.082182509  -0.099324060  -0.071736068\r\n```\r\n\r\n```{coffee}\r\nstpacf(data = series.df, wmatrices = list(NULL, W1, W2, W3))\r\n```\r\n\r\n```{coffee}\r\n      Spatial Lag 0 Spatial Lag 1 Spatial Lag 2 Spatial Lag 3\r\n [1,]   0.530291243   0.016877829   -0.02041068   -0.02259844\r\n [2,]  -0.267840367  -0.125740204   -0.06304123   -0.07979451\r\n [3,]  -0.604128221   0.315954281    0.38922542    0.32970725\r\n [4,]  -0.123407703   0.070889529    0.12937037    0.10441696\r\n [5,]   0.091879237  -0.098668769   -0.11987887   -0.02897873\r\n [6,]  -0.372849714   0.167521646    0.33716061    0.12688059\r\n [7,]  -0.369315531   0.231976407    0.21028689    0.39208167\r\n [8,]   0.146595124  -0.051525250    0.03467336   -0.18545893\r\n [9,]  -0.145156302  -0.065837972   -0.02520312    0.08499030\r\n[10,]  -0.400384626   0.304069457    0.36417232    0.24535678\r\n[11,]   0.001946385   0.005541423    0.05849558    0.05818564\r\n[12,]   0.292550046  -0.215536127   -0.21698865   -0.18467466\r\n[13,]  -0.201015617   0.100634247    0.10037482    0.03982569\r\n[14,]  -0.223525612   0.175065139    0.29037501    0.32549051\r\n[15,]   0.419228790  -0.344807276   -0.46143391   -0.44437612\r\n```\r\n","google":"","note":"Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration."}